				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=14366"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=14364"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Making pacts with other players will create trade routes between both your planets and his planets.<br />
<br />
You get a certain % of the other planet's production. At 0 Commerce CM, you get 10%(11% if allied too)+1%/CM . Each planet can trade with 3 others planets.<br />
<br />
So pacting with rich players(people with lots of URs and Rs) can increase your income by quite a bit.<br />
<br />
Also, if all of the other's planets are already commercing elsewhere, you won't gain anything.<br />
<br />
Breaking pacts will break the trade routes.<br />
<br />
Hope this helps.<p><br>Redjack<br />
A lonesome Cowboy			   <P align=right></P>
